title: Observed Differences Between Argon- And Krypton-Induced Reactions Leading to the Same Compound Nuclei, Er-158 And Er-156

x4freetext: Observed Differences Between Argon- And Krypton-Induced
Reactions Leading to the Same Compound Nuclei, Er-158
And Er-156

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Physical Review, Part C, Nuclear Physics, Vol.10, p.722 (1974)

x4freetext: .Letter from H.Gauvin
. Alice Accelerator at Orsay
.The Energy Degradation was
Calculated According to L.C.Northcliffe Et Al.,
Nucl.Data A7,233(1970).
For a Number of Experiments the Same Energy was
Obtained on the Target by Using Different Charges
For the Incident Ions (AR12+, AR13+ AND KR23+, KR24+,
KR25+) And Different Arrangements For the Aluminium
Or Nickel Degraders. The Good Agreement Between the
Cross Sections Obtained with these Different
Arrangements Constituted a Check of the Energy-Loss
Values Calculated with Northcliffe`S Tables.
.Annular Surface Barrier Detector
Absolute Yields For Er-153 were Obtained in a Separate
Set of Irradiations in an Appropriate Energy Range
With Targets Put Inside a Faraday Cup. Then a
Comparison Between Er-153 Measured in the Helium-Jet
Apparatus and the Tb-149-G (GRANDDAUGHTER OF ER-153)
Measured After Bombardment in the Faraday Cup Gave the
Efficiency of the Collecting System.
The Errors Given are the Statistical
Uncertainties on Counts As Stated by the Authors in
Their Letter.
Numerical Values have Been Reported by the Authors
On Request.
- By CAJAD - Alpha Branching are not Given by Authors.
Probably, Measured Cross Sections Must be Considered As
Relative Ones Only.
Lapf
Some Corrections have Been Included by
CAJAD
Data Heading For Err-Analys is Changed.
Lower Case.
V.Mc-Lane`S Remark For B0036003 is Included
Last checking has been done.
Ge-70, Isotopically Enriched, Containing 6 %
Ge-72 (FOR WHICH THE CROSS SECTIONS WERE CORRECTED),
Thickness About 300 Micrograms/Cm**2 Deposited on Al-
Backing Foils.
